## FEM Analysis

The final wrench geometry was imported into **ANSYS**.  
Boundary conditions followed the schematic: fixed constraint over the **upper 0.40 in of the drive** and torsional loading equivalent to **600 inÂ·lbf**.

### **FEM Outputs**

#### **1. Normal Strain Contours (Gauge Direction)**  
FEM strain fields validated that the reduced section increased strain concentration where gauges are bonded without undesirable stress spikes.

#### **2. Maximum Principal Stress Contour**  
Stresses remained below allowable limits for:

- Yield  
- Fatigue  
- Crack-growth tolerance

#### **3. Load-Point Deflection and Stress Table**
| Quantity | FEM Value |
|---------|-----------|
| Maximum Normal Stress (anywhere) | 133.75 ksi|
| Normal Stress at Probe Location |  |
| Load Point Deflection | 0.38077 in |
| Strains at Gauge Location [x, y, z] | [-0.3059, -0.30605, 1.055] millistrain |

---

## Sensitivity Calculation (mV/V)

Using the FEM-computed strain in a **half-bridge Wheatstone configuration**, the output was evaluated using the standard approximation:

\[
\frac{V_{out}}{V_{in}} \approx \frac{k(2\varepsilon)}{4}, \quad k = \text{gauge factor}
\]

**Final Output Sensitivity:**  
\[
\boxed{\text{â‰¥ 1.0 mV/V at 600 inÂ·lbf}}
\]

This meets the project requirement.

---

## Strain Gauge Selection

A suitable commercial gauge was selected:

**Selected Gauge:** Vishay Micro-Measurements linear foil strain gauge  
**Model:** EA-06-125BZ-350 (350 Î©, GF â‰ˆ 2.05)  
**Product Link:** [Vishay Micro-Measurements EA-06-125BZ-350](https://www.micro-measurements.com)

---

### Gauge Specifications

| **Gauge Parameter**       | **Value**              |
|---------------------------|------------------------|
| Grid Length               | 3.18 mm (0.125 in)     |
| Grid Width                | 1.57 mm (0.062 in)     |
| Pattern Type              | Linear                 |

The Vishay EA-06-125BZ-350 strain gauge was selected because its grid dimensions align with the strain levels predicted by the FEM analysis and the available bonding area on the redesigned torque wrench. This gauge provides reliable sensitivity with stable performance in a half-bridge configuration that gives accurate measurements during torque loading.
---

## Final Remarks

This project demonstrated the full mechanical design workflow:

- Analytical modeling    
- CAD-to-simulation integration  
- Materials and failure-mode validation  
- Sensor-driven mechanical design  

The final torque-wrench design satisfies structural requirements **while surpassing the sensitivity target**, improving the original baseline design by more than a factor of two.

